GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 487
Short Title: Require Legislative Sponsors/Appropriations. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Everitt (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
March 26, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT REQUIRING LEGISLATIVE SPONSORS FOR APPROPRIATIONS ENACTED BY
3 THE CURRENT OPERATIONS APPROPRIATIONS ACT.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 143C-1-2 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 143C-1-2. Appropriations: constitutional requirement; reversions.
7 …
8 (a1) Legislative Sponsor Requirement. – An appropriation enacted in the Current
9 Operations Appropriations Act shall not be legally valid unless (i) the appropriation is sponsored
10 by a member of the General Assembly and (ii) the name of the sponsoring legislator is stated in
11 the text of the appropriation.
12 …."
13 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law.
*S487-v-1*

